The last 3 teams to win the SCT have all been 1st-time champs (Pt Beach, Rumson, MDP) and all of them beat 16-time champ CBA in the final.
With Mater Dei's win tonight, there have now been 7 different SCT champions in the last 7 years and 8 in the last 10.
Mater Dei outscores CBA 32-7 over the final 10 minutes and completes an improbable climb to the SCT title with a 50-43 win over the Colts.
Mater Dei is a runaway train at this point. they lead 46-41 with 24 secs left.
Nyke McCombs with 1:15 left hits the 1st of 2 FTs and we have ourselves an SCT final. 41 all, McCombs to shoot 1 more out of the timeout.
Harris and-1 on the break and Mater Dei has cut it to 4 with 2:24 left. Sam Houston has fouled out for CBA.
3:12 left, CBA leads Mater Dei 41-33 in the boys SCT final.
Steal and reverse dunk by Bryan Harris has cut Mater Dei's deficit to 36-29 with 6:27. Harris leads MDP with 8 off the bench.
Mater Dei scores the last 7 of the quarter and trails CBA 36-25 heading to the 4th. McGuire 13, Andree 11 for CBA.
Andree with back to back buckets and CBA has stretched its lead over Mater Dei to 36-18 with 1:12 left in the 3rd.
CBA up 28-16 with 4:47 left in the 3rd.
That should read 4-14 for Mater Dei from the field.
Mater Dei is 4-18 from the floor and 3-8 from the line. CBA has zoned them up and kept it a half-court game.
CBA leads Mater Dei 26-13 at half. Pat Andree and Jack McGuire have 7 pts each. Elijah Barnes 5 for Mater Dei.
Andree hits his 1st three and CBA has built up a 26-13 lead on Mater Dei with 1:10 left until half. CBA had 24 in last year's entire game.
CBA leads Mater Dei 10-3 after 1. Deliberate pace: Mater Dei is 0-4 from the field, 3-7 from the FT line, and has 5 turnovers.
1:21 left in the 1st and Mater Dei still does not have a field goal, but only trails CBA 8-2. The curse of the MAC is alive and well.
CBA Mater Dei underway.
SJV beats Manasquan 59-48 to win the Shore Conference Tournament for the 1st time since 2005.
Vianney leads Manasquan 54-46 with 1:50 left. Tina Lebron and Kelly Campbell have 14 pts each. Faith Masonius 17 for Squan.
Correction from earlier: this would be 1st Vianney title in 11 years, not 10,
Faith Masonius and Dara Mabrey hit 3s on back-to-back trips and Squan chops Vianney's lead to 47-38 with 4:39 left.
Stella Clark at the buzzer again to end the 3rd, but Vianney leads Manasquan 41-27, 8 mins away from 1st SCT title in 10 years.
SJV has built a 34-23 lead on Manasquan with 2:54 left. Tina Lebron just banged back-to-back threes and has 11 to lead Vianney.
Vanessa Pinho has done a good job on Stella Clark (2 pts) when she's been in the game. She's been the stopper for the Lancers this tourny.
SJV leads Manasquan 22-17 at half. Kimi Evans has 6, Tina Lebron 5. Dara Mabrey leads Squan with 5.
SJV leads Manasquan 13-9 after 1. Stella Clark with and-1 at the buzzer but misses the FT.
